    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In my opinion, “sourceCompatibility” means the what feature you can use in your source code.For example,if you set sourceCompatibility to 1.7, then you can't use lambda expression which a new feature in java 8 even though you jdk version is 1.8.<br>\nAs for “targetCompatibility”, it means which version of jre the generated class file can be run on, if you set it to 1.8,it may not run successfully on jdk 1.7, but it can usually run on higher version of jdk.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
